TCGA-D7-A4YU,TCGA-D7-A4YU.DF435B0E-B010-4911-9123-4AECDA1B0EDE,"PESEL: : XXX. Gender: M. Examination result No. Unit in charge: 1. ef. no. Clinical diagnosis (suspicion): malignancy of the stomach - Stomach, undefined - Gastric cancer. Date of admission: (urgency: Standard). Material: 1) Material: stomach, Method of collection: Total organ resection. Histopathological Diagnosis: Tubular and partially mucinous adenocarcinoma of the stomach. Cancer metastases in the. lymph nodes NO XI/XXV. G3, pT3, pN3a Mixed type sec. (8140/3 T-63000). Macroscopic description: The specimen containing the stomach, after being incised along the greater curvature sized: 21.5 x 11 cm. with the omentum sized: 40 x 23 cm. Ulcerous tumour in the region of the lesser curvature sized 5.5 x 1.2 x 1.1 cm. Distance from the proximal. end: 1.5 cm, from distal end: 9.5 cm. Another, elevated tumour in the greater curvature region. 3.5 x 2.3 x 1,5 cm, 5.5 cm from the proximal line. and 6.5 cm from the distal line. Microscopic description: Adenocarcinoma tubulare partim mucocellulare G3 bifocale. Tumour penetrates the full thickness of the stomach wall and perigastric fat tissue. Surgical incision lines and the omentum free of neoplastic lesions. Signs of vascular invasion. Lymph nodes: - lesser curvature: metastases carcinomatosae in lymphonodis NO V/XII. Infiltratio carcinomatosa. capsulae lymphonodorum et telae adiposae perinodalis. - greater curvature: metastases carcinomatosae in lymphonodis No IV/VIII. Infiltratio carcinomatosa. capsulae lymphonodorum. peripyloric: metastases carcinomatosae in lymphonodis No II/V. Infiltratio. carcinomatosa capsulae lymphonodorum. Result of immunohistochemical examination: HER2 protein stained with Ventana's Pathway HER-2/neu (4B5) Rabbit Monoclonal Antibody. Negative reaction in invasive cancerous cells ( Score = 0). CONTACT YOUR DOCTOR WITH THIS.",III,Unknown,BLCA,189.0,TCGA-D7-A4YU-01Z-00-DX1.42DF1586-BD02-4482-AEAF-8F2C1BBB1C20.svs,73.0,D7,16.66666666666666