TCGA-D7-8572,TCGA-D7-8572.4862ab6e-432e-4cce-ba69-df7400475559,"Material: 1) Material: stomach, Method of collection: Total organ resection. Histopathological diagnosis: Adenocarcinoma of the Stomach (G2, pT2, pNO). Macroscopic description: The specimen consisting of the stomach sized 25 X 17 cm with the omentum sized 30 X 20 cm. Tumour. sized 9 X 5.5 X 1.4 cm found in the central part. The distance from the proximal boundary is 12 cm, from. distal boundary, 1 cm. Microscopic description: Adenocarcinoma (papillary cystic; G2 - intestinal type according to the Lauren classification) - the tumour infiltrates. deep into the muscular membrane (pT2). Incision lines, omentum and nodes (10) - free of neoplastic lesions.",II,Unknown,BLCA,174.0,TCGA-D7-8572-01Z-00-DX1.E7F9367F-14C4-4561-934D-AE7A778CD13C.svs,57.0,D7,17.033333333333335,17.033333333333335,17.033333333333335,1.0,1.0,1.0,0.0,STAD,1.0
