TCGA-VQ-AA69,TCGA-VQ-AA69.3B8DBFF7-A3D6-42AF-B721-919D0B2E88E0,"PRIMARY SITE: Stomach (Gastroesophageal junction). 1- ""Product of esophagogastrectomy"": Undifferentiated carcinoma associated with moderately differentiated adenocarcinoma of. gastroesophageal junction (measuring 12.6 cm), infiltrating up to perigastric adipose tissue. Note: Most of the tumor is located in the stomach, extending to the esophagus. Presence of foci of Angiolymphatic vascular invasion. Surgical margins free of neoplasia. Metastases in six lymph nodes (6/37): one from chain 2, three from chain 3, two from chain 9 (with. Extranodal invasion). 2 - ""Greater omentum"": Absence of neoplasia. 3 - ""Esophageal margin"": Absence of neoplasia. Note: See immunohistochemical study.",III,Unknown,BLCA,333.0,TCGA-VQ-AA69-01Z-00-DX1.1EEF2AD7-6470-44B5-9E87-E77AE47262F0.svs,35.0,VQ,28.8,28.8,28.8,1.0,1.0,1.0,0.0,STAD,1.0
