TCGA-D7-6524,TCGA-D7-6524.c0b8a70d-b8b4-4c81-bb96-9038b66a1da1,"page 1 / 1. Examination: Histopathological examination. Material: Total resection of organ - stomach. Expected time of examination: Clinical diagnosis: Cancer of the pyloric part of the stomach. Macroscopic description: The tested material contained the stomach, after having been excised along the greater curvature sized 20.4 x 18.8 cm. A. thickened wall sized 10.6 x 11.7 cm found in the parapyloric region, 1.2 cm to the proximal boundary, 1.1 cm to the distal. boundary. Microscopic description: Adenocarcinoma invasivum (G3) ventriculi. The neoplastic invasion spreads the full thickness of the stomach wall penetrating into the fat tissue. The incision line in the esophagus is free of hyperplasia at the side of the pylorus within the neoplastic proliferation. (Mixed. type according to Laurén's classification). Outside tumour: gastritis chronica. Omentum - hyperaeinia. Lymph nodes: (pericardium): metastases carcinomatosae in lyniphonodo No (I /1). (lesser curvature): metastases carcinomatosae in. lymphonodis No (III /VIII). (greater curvature): metastases carcinomatosae in lymphonodis No (II / VI). (peripylorum): lymphonodulitis reactiva No 1. Histopathological diagnosis: Adenocarcinoma invasivum ventriculi (G3), pT2, ,pNfivasive-adenocarcinoma of the stomach.7. Metastases carcinomatosae in lymphonodis No VI / XVI. Cancer metastases in the lymph nodes.",II,Unknown,BLCA,153.0,TCGA-D7-6524-01Z-00-DX1.ec1248f6-7d22-49c5-8300-673d25819e1d.svs,53.0,D7,18.1,18.1,18.1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,DSTAD,1.0
TCGA-D7-6524,TCGA-D7-6524.c0b8a70d-b8b4-4c81-bb96-9038b66a1da1,"page 1 / 1. Examination: Histopathological examination. Material: Total resection of organ - stomach. Expected time of examination: Clinical diagnosis: Cancer of the pyloric part of the stomach. Macroscopic description: The tested material contained the stomach, after having been excised along the greater curvature sized 20.4 x 18.8 cm. A. thickened wall sized 10.6 x 11.7 cm found in the parapyloric region, 1.2 cm to the proximal boundary, 1.1 cm to the distal. boundary. Microscopic description: Adenocarcinoma invasivum (G3) ventriculi. The neoplastic invasion spreads the full thickness of the stomach wall penetrating into the fat tissue. The incision line in the esophagus is free of hyperplasia at the side of the pylorus within the neoplastic proliferation. (Mixed. type according to Laurén's classification). Outside tumour: gastritis chronica. Omentum - hyperaeinia. Lymph nodes: (pericardium): metastases carcinomatosae in lyniphonodo No (I /1). (lesser curvature): metastases carcinomatosae in. lymphonodis No (III /VIII). (greater curvature): metastases carcinomatosae in lymphonodis No (II / VI). (peripylorum): lymphonodulitis reactiva No 1. Histopathological diagnosis: Adenocarcinoma invasivum ventriculi (G3), pT2, ,pNfivasive-adenocarcinoma of the stomach.7. Metastases carcinomatosae in lymphonodis No VI / XVI. Cancer metastases in the lymph nodes.",II,Unknown,BLCA,154.0,TCGA-D7-6524-01Z-00-DX2.6E8242FF-FAF3-4CAA-9CB2-CE0BC1D518C9.svs,53.0,D7,18.1,18.1,18.1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,DSTAD,1.0
